1
00:00:01,493 --> 00:00:04,757
Hey there, everyone!

2
00:00:06,019 --> 00:00:07,100
I'm Tsumi.

3
00:00:07,140 --> 00:00:08,269
Hi, I'm Batsu.

4
00:00:08,309 --> 00:00:11,522
We're a married manzai duo
on the verge of breaking up.

5
00:00:11,562 --> 00:00:15,015
- You came up with a funny bit today, right?
- Yep, nailed it.

6
00:00:15,055 --> 00:00:19,005
We'll show you the faces and voices
we'd make right before we come.

7
00:00:19,045 --> 00:00:21,132
I just did it with Koichi Sato.

8
00:00:21,172 --> 00:00:24,199
Oh no, I'm coming! Squeeze.

9
00:00:24,239 --> 00:00:27,251
Hey there, everyone!

10
00:00:27,291 --> 00:00:29,724
- I'm Tsumi.
- Hi, I'm Batsu.

11
00:00:29,764 --> 00:00:33,960
Together, we're called Dostoevsky!

12
00:00:34,163 --> 00:00:36,313
I just did it with Jennifer Lawrence.

13
00:00:36,353 --> 00:00:38,800
Ahhh, ngh.

14
00:00:38,801 --> 00:00:41,661
Oh no... I'm coming, ohhh!

15
00:00:41,713 --> 00:00:43,998
I just did it with Cameron Diaz.

16
00:00:44,038 --> 00:00:47,366
Ahhh, guh!

17
00:01:04,840 --> 00:01:08,526
And finally,
the day of the audition arrived.

18
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:17,327
I felt like Rocky
before his fight with Apollo.

19
00:01:17,813 --> 00:01:23,207
Rocky stepped into the ring,
certain he could never beat Apollo.

20
00:01:23,573 --> 00:01:29,847
I, too, had a meaningless certainty
that our act would absolutely bomb.

21
00:01:44,460 --> 00:01:48,522
But there was one big difference
between me and Rocky.

22
00:01:54,276 --> 00:01:55,953
Oh, you're up.

23
00:01:56,730 --> 00:01:59,110
This is bad. I'm crazy nervous.

24
00:02:01,603 --> 00:02:02,863
Me, too.

25
00:02:02,903 --> 00:02:04,970
Don't you dare get nervous.

26
00:02:05,509 --> 00:02:13,295
Rocky fought a battle he knew he'd lose
to prove he wasn't just a lowlife.

27
00:02:13,631 --> 00:02:16,698
But by dragging Chika into this fight,

28
00:02:16,733 --> 00:02:21,858
I felt like I was only proving
that I really am just a lowlife.

29
00:02:24,465 --> 00:02:27,220
Alright, I'm gonna go
get a little more sleep.

30
00:02:27,260 --> 00:02:28,558
Okay.

31
00:02:36,092 --> 00:02:38,995
Alright!

32
00:02:41,664 --> 00:02:43,164
Ta-da!

33
00:02:43,554 --> 00:02:45,306
Yay!

34
00:02:45,563 --> 00:02:47,251
Thank you!

35
00:02:49,836 --> 00:02:51,316
Here we go!

36
00:02:58,561 --> 00:03:02,034
- Shall we have some action tonight?
- I'm so glad to be alive!

37
00:03:28,531 --> 00:03:31,376
I Still Want to Do It with My Wife

38
00:03:31,416 --> 00:03:34,683
Taro, hold the fort, okay?
Mommy and Daddy will do their best.

39
00:03:34,723 --> 00:03:35,805
Episode 11: Am I stupid?

40
00:03:35,845 --> 00:03:37,605
I wanna come watch, too.

41
00:03:37,645 --> 00:03:41,770
Sorry, Taro. But it'd be embarrassing
if you saw Mommy and Daddy perform.

42
00:03:41,810 --> 00:03:43,723
We didn’t go watch you either, did we?

43
00:03:43,763 --> 00:03:45,729
In exchange, you can use the iPad all day.

44
00:03:45,769 --> 00:03:47,170
- Really?
- Yep.

45
00:03:47,210 --> 00:03:48,623
Okay, good luck!

46
00:03:50,476 --> 00:03:51,536
All right, we're off!

47
00:03:51,576 --> 00:03:53,496
- Bye-bye!
- See ya later!

48
00:03:53,870 --> 00:03:55,437
Right, let's go.

49
00:03:56,810 --> 00:03:59,449
What is it? Get moving, come on.

50
00:04:06,668 --> 00:04:10,806
Maybe we should've let Taro
come watch us do comedy.

51
00:04:10,846 --> 00:04:13,651
Are you crazy? Not with that routine. No way.

52
00:04:14,199 --> 00:04:18,137
But he watches Doburock all the time.
He's probably immune to dirty jokes.

53
00:04:18,153 --> 00:04:20,293
Our act is way cruder than Doburock.

54
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:21,749
You think so?

55
00:04:21,875 --> 00:04:24,255
Wait, is that a compliment?

56
00:04:24,268 --> 00:04:27,485
Hell no! Why would you even think that?
Are you stupid?

57
00:04:54,793 --> 00:04:56,750
- Hello.
- Hello, ma'am.

58
00:05:00,330 --> 00:05:01,542
Yes.

59
00:05:04,740 --> 00:05:09,060
- D-Dost...
- Dos-to-ev... Just a sec. It's Dostoevsky.

60
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:11,950
- So, you're Dostoevsky?
- Dostoevsky, yes.

61
00:05:14,671 --> 00:05:15,793
- Yes.
- Okay.

62
00:05:15,833 --> 00:05:16,860
Thank you.

63
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:20,172
Please come back here at least
30 minutes before the audition.

64
00:05:20,212 --> 00:05:21,212
Got it.

65
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:23,689
- We'll go in sign-up order.
- Okay, thank you.

66
00:05:23,729 --> 00:05:25,293
Good luck.

67
00:05:25,432 --> 00:05:27,446
Move it, you're in the way!

68
00:05:30,083 --> 00:05:32,506
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

69
00:05:35,097 --> 00:05:39,880
So... I just did it with Ken Takakura!
Oh no, I'm coming! Squeeze.

70
00:05:39,948 --> 00:05:45,173
Um, I just did it with Ken Takakura!
Oh no, I'm coming! Squeeze.

71
00:05:46,748 --> 00:05:49,220
Hey, your line's up next!

72
00:05:49,349 --> 00:05:51,946
Oh, sorry... who was the next one?

73
00:05:52,189 --> 00:05:54,296
Huh? Mitsu Dan, obviously.

74
00:05:54,336 --> 00:05:56,782
Are you okay?
You've had no energy this whole time.

75
00:05:56,822 --> 00:05:59,717
I'm just nervous, so I feel a bit sick.

76
00:05:59,944 --> 00:06:03,200
Get it together.
This whole thing was your idea.

77
00:06:03,768 --> 00:06:05,067
Seriously.

78
00:06:06,670 --> 00:06:07,984
I'm gonna buy another one.

79
00:06:08,024 --> 00:06:11,017
- You want to drink more?
- I'm nervous too, you know!

80
00:06:12,723 --> 00:06:14,516
Ow, damn it.

81
00:06:23,902 --> 00:06:25,252
Come on, hurry up.

82
00:06:30,132 --> 00:06:31,564
Alright.

83
00:06:41,086 --> 00:06:43,363
Stop making that face.

84
00:06:44,310 --> 00:06:46,420
Pull yourself together.

85
00:06:57,292 --> 00:07:00,952
Okay, okay, settle down, please.

86
00:07:02,013 --> 00:07:06,720
Thank you all for coming here today.

87
00:07:06,858 --> 00:07:10,022
We'll now be starting the audition.

88
00:07:10,035 --> 00:07:17,101
We're hoping to select two
or maybe three acts from you all.

89
00:07:17,193 --> 00:07:22,481
Those selected will perform
in the live show starting at 6 pm.

90
00:07:22,822 --> 00:07:28,262
Some people have gone professional from here,
so if that's your goal, give it your all.

91
00:07:28,407 --> 00:07:32,373
Our judges will be
these distinguished comedy writers here.

92
00:07:32,413 --> 00:07:35,269
- That's enough of that.
- They worked on
The God Tongue
.

93
00:07:35,738 --> 00:07:37,622
No, that was Gogoro.

94
00:07:37,946 --> 00:07:39,491
He's tall, too.

95
00:07:39,531 --> 00:07:40,748
Same thing, really.

96
00:07:41,185 --> 00:07:43,489
Well then, let's go in sign-up order.

97
00:07:43,529 --> 00:07:44,942
Let me see...

98
00:07:45,432 --> 00:07:47,545
- The Water Flees?
- Yes!

99
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:49,120
- Water Flees!
- Yes!

100
00:07:49,160 --> 00:07:50,640
Go ahead, please.

101
00:07:53,559 --> 00:07:55,260
- Good luck.
- Thank you, sir!

102
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:56,509
Here we go!

103
00:07:59,569 --> 00:08:03,073
- Hi everyone!
- Hi!

104
00:08:03,113 --> 00:08:06,310
- Hi, we're the Water Flees!
- Thanks for having us!

105
00:08:06,350 --> 00:08:10,917
Um, I really love baseball clinics,
so I'm gonna do one.

106
00:08:10,957 --> 00:08:14,294
What's your 50-meter dash time?

107
00:08:14,303 --> 00:08:15,642
50-meter dash time, huh?

108
00:08:15,682 --> 00:08:17,520
15 seconds!

109
00:08:17,770 --> 00:08:19,819
- Well, kids are usually—
- That's slow!

110
00:08:19,859 --> 00:08:22,073
Don't be so blunt! It's mean!

111
00:08:22,113 --> 00:08:25,655
- What's Isao Harimoto's dash time?
- A pro's dash time, huh.

112
00:08:25,695 --> 00:08:28,183
- 14.9 seconds.
- That's barely any different!

113
00:08:28,223 --> 00:08:30,714
This blond guy's been stalking me.

114
00:08:30,716 --> 00:08:31,934
Huh?

115
00:08:32,090 --> 00:08:35,037
- Toshi!
- You were a stalker?!

116
00:08:35,210 --> 00:08:37,694
Can't believe you're going to Tokyo, but—

117
00:08:37,734 --> 00:08:40,725
C'mon, get pumped! Get pumped!
Let's go! Here we go!

118
00:08:40,765 --> 00:08:43,071
Come at me! Low and hard, come on!

119
00:08:43,111 --> 00:08:45,516
What kinda throw was that?
Try to knock me out!

120
00:08:45,556 --> 00:08:46,610
Come on, gather here!

121
00:08:46,650 --> 00:08:48,387
And next up...

122
00:08:49,150 --> 00:08:50,790
The Knock on the Knee duo!

123
00:08:50,830 --> 00:08:53,070
Knock-knock, knock-knock,
knock on the knee!

124
00:08:53,110 --> 00:08:55,236
Thanks, we were Knock on the Knee!

125
00:08:59,566 --> 00:09:02,433
One more time for Knock on the Knee!

126
00:09:02,473 --> 00:09:04,039
Please exit the stage.

127
00:09:04,180 --> 00:09:05,460
Thank you!

128
00:09:05,476 --> 00:09:08,257
And next up is...

129
00:09:08,697 --> 00:09:12,002
D-D-Dostoevsky!

130
00:09:12,159 --> 00:09:13,806
- Yes! Here!
- Dostoevsky, please.

131
00:09:13,846 --> 00:09:15,627
That's us, Dostoevsky. Yes.

132
00:09:16,093 --> 00:09:17,789
Come, we're on.

133
00:09:27,933 --> 00:09:30,379
Get it together. You wanted results, right?

134
00:09:33,420 --> 00:09:34,439
Hey!

135
00:09:34,479 --> 00:09:36,055
Yeah... okay.

136
00:09:36,760 --> 00:09:40,325
- Whenever you're ready.
- Right. Let's go.

137
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:41,525
Wait.

138
00:09:41,565 --> 00:09:42,606
Huh?

139
00:09:42,646 --> 00:09:44,292
Embrace me.

140
00:09:44,296 --> 00:09:46,339
What are you saying?!

141
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:48,983
I'm nervous too, you know. Let's do this.

142
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:51,860
Hey there, everyone!

143
00:09:51,900 --> 00:09:53,085
I'm Tsumi!

144
00:09:53,125 --> 00:09:55,999
Hi, I am... Batsu.

145
00:09:56,072 --> 00:09:57,532
-Together we are...
-We are...

146
00:09:57,572 --> 00:10:01,397
Dostoevsky!

147
00:10:02,379 --> 00:10:05,067
You were totally late, idiot!

148
00:10:05,372 --> 00:10:07,560
Uh, how did it go again?

149
00:10:07,626 --> 00:10:09,514
Don't give me that.

150
00:10:09,888 --> 00:10:13,928
So believe it or not, we're actually
suffering from a loss of libido.

151
00:10:13,968 --> 00:10:18,920
- We don't just have less of it. We lost it.
- Yeah, yeah, loss... Los Lobos.

152
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:20,755
What are you even saying?

153
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:27,382
So we decided to each pick our favorite
celebrity and imagine doing it with them.

154
00:10:27,422 --> 00:10:29,106
Yeah. Doing it. Doing it.

155
00:10:29,180 --> 00:10:33,120
Speak up! That's supposed
to be your line anyway!

156
00:10:33,159 --> 00:10:35,137
Like, you're into Mitsu Dan, right?

157
00:10:35,177 --> 00:10:40,320
So you'll show everyone the face
you'd make after doing it with Mitsu Dan.

158
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:42,240
No, I can't...

159
00:10:42,280 --> 00:10:44,200
Don't give me that!

160
00:10:44,253 --> 00:10:45,860
Fine, I'll go first then.

161
00:10:45,900 --> 00:10:48,126
So, I absolutely love Koichi Sato.

162
00:10:48,166 --> 00:10:53,280
I just did it with Koichi Sato!
Oh no, I'm coming! Squeeze!

163
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:58,004
What are you doing? It's your turn!

164
00:10:58,669 --> 00:11:02,196
Da-Dan... Dan...

165
00:11:02,213 --> 00:11:06,040
I just did it with Mitsu Dan... Squeeze.

166
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:12,333
I just did it with Hugh Jackman!
Oh no, I'm coming! Hew-hew, baby!

167
00:11:14,740 --> 00:11:17,047
It's your turn!

168
00:11:20,939 --> 00:11:27,899
I just did it with Brad Pitt!
Oh no, I'm coming! Pew pew!

169
00:11:29,780 --> 00:11:36,280
I just did it with DiCaprio!
Oh no, I'm coming! Titanic!

170
00:11:36,640 --> 00:11:42,920
I just did it with Ken Takakura!
Oh no, I'm coming! He's so clumsy!

171
00:11:44,010 --> 00:11:50,230
I just did it with Shohei Uno!
Oh no! Too cute! Blegh!

172
00:12:28,037 --> 00:12:35,632
I thought I'd be better off dead.

173
00:12:39,958 --> 00:12:46,640
I just did it with Hugh Jackman again!
Oh no, I'm coming! Squeeze!

174
00:12:52,446 --> 00:12:54,426
Thank you very much!

175
00:12:59,846 --> 00:13:03,153
Oh, um... thank you!

176
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:07,180
- Well then, please exit the stage.
- Okay.

177
00:13:11,420 --> 00:13:13,500
All right, next up, um...

178
00:13:14,646 --> 00:13:20,510
- I'm thinking of taking up judo at my age.
- Judo at your age? That's unusual.

179
00:13:20,550 --> 00:13:25,230
- And I think the very first move is crucial.
- Yeah, it is everything.

180
00:14:17,715 --> 00:14:19,179
What's wrong?

181
00:14:20,942 --> 00:14:22,872
What am I doing?

182
00:14:27,052 --> 00:14:28,652
What is this?

183
00:14:31,788 --> 00:14:33,802
Am I stupid?

184
00:14:37,640 --> 00:14:39,335
This...

185
00:14:40,926 --> 00:14:43,130
This isn't my life.

186
00:14:45,898 --> 00:14:50,490
It's not like I had big goals or anything.

187
00:14:50,530 --> 00:14:52,340
So what the hell is this?

188
00:14:58,979 --> 00:15:00,436
Why?

189
00:15:00,826 --> 00:15:02,921
I work to cover for you.

190
00:15:04,394 --> 00:15:09,143
And for what? Is this some punishment?
Is my whole life some sort of punishment?

191
00:15:09,833 --> 00:15:11,273
That's not true.

192
00:15:13,879 --> 00:15:15,387
But...

193
00:15:17,967 --> 00:15:21,933
This happened because I didn't
live my life right.

194
00:15:24,085 --> 00:15:26,119
I don't think that's true.

195
00:15:27,903 --> 00:15:29,983
I know it, deep down.

196
00:15:30,639 --> 00:15:32,912
I've been looking the other way,

197
00:15:32,925 --> 00:15:34,012
from my own life.

198
00:15:34,052 --> 00:15:36,612
Nobody knows that better than me!

199
00:15:39,849 --> 00:15:41,156
But...

200
00:15:42,312 --> 00:15:44,483
Why the hell did I end up with you?

201
00:15:45,357 --> 00:15:47,613
Seriously, what are you?

202
00:15:47,626 --> 00:15:50,626
Who even are you? Get it together!

203
00:15:52,250 --> 00:15:55,109
You said you'd get results.

204
00:15:55,789 --> 00:15:57,408
And what was that?

205
00:15:57,796 --> 00:15:59,747
How did we end up like this?

206
00:16:00,030 --> 00:16:02,435
You should try harder. Harder!

207
00:16:05,318 --> 00:16:06,684
I...

208
00:16:08,519 --> 00:16:10,184
I'm so frustrated.

209
00:16:10,286 --> 00:16:12,188
So damn frustrated.

210
00:16:13,294 --> 00:16:16,745
'Cause I thought you were
the greatest, you know?

211
00:16:20,162 --> 00:16:23,052
Aren't I so damn pathetic?

212
00:16:31,765 --> 00:16:33,594
But I didn't have the guts.

213
00:16:36,173 --> 00:16:38,686
I was just whining
about my life all the time.

214
00:16:41,030 --> 00:16:43,076
I'm pathetic.

215
00:16:47,196 --> 00:16:48,871
This is your fault.

216
00:16:50,256 --> 00:16:51,717
Or actually...

217
00:16:52,350 --> 00:16:55,730
I'm the pathetic one
blaming you for everything.

218
00:16:55,849 --> 00:16:57,642
Actually, it's all my fault.

219
00:16:57,682 --> 00:17:00,992
It's all my fault for not living my own life.

220
00:17:03,055 --> 00:17:04,822
But you know what?

221
00:17:05,590 --> 00:17:07,640
You pull yourself together, too!

222
00:17:07,801 --> 00:17:09,455
Just do it!

223
00:17:09,523 --> 00:17:12,910
Don't make me tell you that! I don't wanna.

224
00:17:16,906 --> 00:17:19,794
God, I'm so pathetic.

225
00:17:21,559 --> 00:17:24,320
A hundred times more pathetic than you.

226
00:18:22,516 --> 00:18:27,578
Fifteen years and ten months ago

227
00:18:40,960 --> 00:18:42,527
Welcome back. How'd it go?

228
00:18:43,568 --> 00:18:45,033
It...

229
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:47,965
didn't work out again.

230
00:18:50,065 --> 00:18:51,404
I see.

231
00:18:52,532 --> 00:18:53,737
Yeah.

232
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:56,677
I thought it was funny, though.

233
00:18:58,943 --> 00:19:01,021
What could have gone wrong?

234
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:05,220
I'm so frustrated.

235
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:08,707
So frustrated.

236
00:19:10,679 --> 00:19:13,355
But you must feel it even more, Gota.

237
00:20:53,149 --> 00:20:54,972
Taro, we're home.

238
00:20:55,012 --> 00:20:57,759
Welcome back. How'd it go?

239
00:20:57,799 --> 00:20:59,802
Yeah. It was fun.

240
00:21:00,322 --> 00:21:01,616
Got any laughs?

241
00:21:01,656 --> 00:21:03,225
Not really.

242
00:21:03,265 --> 00:21:07,608
That's why I told you, you should've
done the flag-raising game.

243
00:21:07,648 --> 00:21:09,424
Yeah, you're right.

244
00:21:09,630 --> 00:21:11,528
I'm hungry.

245
00:21:11,649 --> 00:21:13,150
I'll make something.

246
00:21:13,847 --> 00:21:16,770
Mama's tired, so she's gonna
take a bath first, okay?

247
00:21:16,810 --> 00:21:18,249
Okay.

248
00:21:19,282 --> 00:21:24,010
Oh, right! You said if it bombed,
I could join Doburock's fan club, right?

249
00:21:44,659 --> 00:21:50,140
I decided to try writing
a screenplay for the first time in a while.

250
00:21:52,239 --> 00:21:54,867
I wanted to write about Chika.

251
00:21:56,353 --> 00:21:59,838
I wanted to write a story
about how she is the best,

252
00:21:59,982 --> 00:22:05,593
yet also the worst person at the same time.

253
00:22:14,865 --> 00:22:15,865
Next Episode Preview

254
00:22:15,891 --> 00:22:17,458
I'm gonna live however I want.

255
00:22:17,498 --> 00:22:20,605
If you keep putting on airs,
it won't resonate with anyone.

256
00:22:20,694 --> 00:22:24,746
I figured maybe we just
have to do it.

257
00:22:24,753 --> 00:22:26,693
I don't care what happens to you.

258
